  "title": "(Internship)Business Assistant/Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Salary Range：</strong>12~25 per hour<br /><strong>Location: </strong>Near MRT stations of Telok Ayer, Downtown, Shenton Way and Raffles Place<br /><strong>Internship Type: </strong>Part-time Internship(≥ 3 days per week preferred)<br /><strong>Reports To: </strong>CEO<br /><strong>Duration: </strong>3–6 months (flexible, open to extension)<br /><strong>Working Arrangement:</strong> Onsite / Hybrid<br /><strong>Industry: </strong>Medical, with the parent company listed in China (Shanghai Stock Exchange A-share). <br /></p><h2>1. <strong>About the Role </strong></h2><p>We are looking for a <strong>detail-oriented and responsible intern</strong> to support our corporate and tax compliance team. This role is well-suited for <strong>university undergraduates</strong> who want hands-on exposure to <strong>Singapore government incentive programs</strong> and <strong>corporate administration work</strong>.</p><p>The intern will assist primarily with <strong>document organising</strong>, <strong>form preparation</strong>, and <strong>administrative support</strong> relating to <strong>EDB tax incentive programs</strong> and other regulatory filings, and other ad hoc tasks assigned by CEO.<br /></p><h2>2. <strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h2><p>Ø Assist in organizing and maintaining corporate and tax-related documents (softcopy & hardcopy)</p><p>Ø Support the preparation and filling of application forms for EDB tax incentive programs and other government incentive-related filings, including liaison internally to collect required supporting documents (e.g. contracts, invoices,& other records)</p><p>Ø Help with data entry, reconciliation, and cross-checking of information in forms and schedules</p><p>Ø Assist in basic drafting of cover letters, checklists, and submission trackers</p><p>Ø Perform other general administrative and ad-hoc tasks assigned by CEO and other colleagues<br /></p><h2>3. <u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></h2><p>Ø Current undergraduate student from Singapore local universities, preferred majors: Accounting, Business, Finance, Economics, Law, Public Policy, or Operation</p><p>Ø Able to commit at least 3 months with immediate start</p><p>Ø Strong attention to detail and organised working style</p><p>Ø Proficient in Microsoft Office software (Word, Excel, PowerPoint).</p><p>Ø Good written and spoken English (Chinese is a plus but not mandatory)</p><p>Ø Responsible, discreet, and able to handle confidential information</p><p>Ø Good command of writing and speaking in both Mandarin and English is preferred.</p>",
